          "type": "text",
          "text": " is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server. Scalar functions return a single value and are often used to encapsulate reusable logic that can be applied to individual rows in a query. This function is designed to determine whether a new meter is identified as non-NYPA (New York Power Authority) based on specific criteria."
